+#### `ses.setWebNotificationHandler(handler)` _Experimental_
+
+* `handler` Function | null
+  * `notification` [WebNotification](web-notification.md)
+
+Sets the handler used to observe and control Web Notifications created in this
+session. Passing `null` removes the handler.
+
+The handler receives notifications created by page or frame code with
+`new Notification()` and persistent notifications created by service workers
+with `ServiceWorkerRegistration.showNotification()`.
+
+If no handler is set, Electron displays notifications with the default native
+notification behavior. If a handler is set and the notification should not be
+shown by Electron automatically, call
+[`notification.suppress()`](web-notification.md#notificationsuppress) before the
+handler returns. The notification can still be controlled later with methods
+such as [`notification.click()`](web-notification.md#notificationclick),
+[`notification.clickAction(action)`](web-notification.md#notificationclickactionaction),
+[`notification.reply(text[, action])`](web-notification.md#notificationreplytext-action),
+and [`notification.close([options])`](web-notification.md#notificationcloseoptions).
+
+```js
+const { session } = require('electron')
+
+session.defaultSession.setWebNotificationHandler((notification) => {
+  notification.suppress()
+
+  notification.on('action', (event) => {
+    console.log('action clicked:', event.action)
+  })
+
+  sendToRemoteAgent({
+    id: notification.id,
+    title: notification.title,
+    body: notification.body,
+    actions: notification.actions
+  })
+})
+```
+
